n the Valley Edmonton regions there are exposed Horseshoe Canyon facies Other formations have been recorded as well the Milk River Foremost Formations However these latter two have a lower diversity of documented dinosaurs primarily due to their lower total fossil quantity neglect from collectors are hindered by the isolation scarcity of exposed outcrops Their dinosaur fossils are primarily teeth recovered from microvertebrate fossil sites Additional geologic formations that have produced only few fossils are the River Group Mary River Formations of the southwest the northwestern Formation The Wapiti Formations two Pachyrhinosaurus bone beds that break its general trend of low productivity The Formation represents strata deposited a transgression Dinosaurs are known from this Formation represent specimens washed to sea or reworked from older sedimentsRyan M J Russell A P 2001 Dinosaurs of Alberta exclusive of Aves In Mesozoic Vertebrate Life edited by Tanke D H Carpenter K Indiana University Press pp 279297 Friendship partners Alberta has relationships with several provinces states and other entities worldwideAlberta Twinning Relationships Retrieved on 12 Aug 2011 Jalisco Mexico Special Relationships Hokkaido Japan Special Relationships Gyeongsangnamdo Korea Special Relationships KhantyMansi Russia Special Relationships YamaloNenets Russia Special Relationships Neuqun Argentina Economic MOUs Mpumalanga Africa Governance Projects Heilongjiang Republic of China Special Relationships Tyumen Russia Special Relationships Montana States of America Transboundary Partnerships Gangwondo Korea Special RelationshipsSee also References Further reading postscript postscript postscript postscript postscript postscript External links Government of Alberta website Provincial Archives of Alberta website Travel Alberta Alberta Encyclopedia CBC Digital ArchivesStriking Oil in Alberta CBC Digital ArchivesElecting Dynasties Alberta Campaigns 1935 to 2001 CBC Digital ArchivesAlberta 100l